originalText.text:
I have lived here for almost 2 1/2 years and had some bad experiences within the building and management. I can safely say that it has been a breathe of fresh air dealing with the new property manager and staff. They have hired new doormen, new super, and porters. The property was a mess and getting repairs done was a task by its self. The new team has been great to deal with. We had an issue with our ac and leaks. The super and property manager were onsite within an hour working on replacing it. It was great to see the interaction and how he was  advising the new staff. The property is undergoing some serious renovation but I am sure his promises will be kept.
The building is a lot cleaner and extermination is provided once you sign up. The move out process was not an hassle and this guys phone seems to be on all the time and he answers!

originalText.text: FINALLY! It's nice to have a management team that actually cares about the tenants.  They're always onsite and quick to address issues. You don't have to wait for days to get a call back and they are the nicest people. Sonny the property manager is great and promised to make renovations throughout Sky East. So far they're living up to their promises.

originalText.text: I reside at sky East  for 1yr and half, its a beautiful building on the outside great comon space, for a few months I did not have the best experience,  the staff didn't cater to their tenants needs, I wasn't the only one that had a bad experience.  The past few months I must say I see a dramatic change for the better, New managent has step up and doing alot work, alot Renovations is taking place throughout the hallways and the appartments. The place is kept clean 24/7 inside and outside, the new staff are much friendlier and attentive. When you get a fallow up visit from management member Sonny  its makes one feel special,  I appreciate them for all their hard work so far,   they are providing  a welcoming,  clean and safe environment for their tenants. The doorman very friendly and polite, team member David and Ryan very polite young men. Keep up the great work.

originalText.text:
WORST BUILDING IN NEW YORK!!! If I could give ZERO stars I would. Move here if you want to pay tons of money for a bed bug infested apartment building with broken appliances. Management doesn't fix anything, be prepared to get the runaround. No AC in the summer (even though they claim to have a unit in every apartment - they are all broken!).

Oh and you WILL get bed bugs at least four times a year. The whole building is infested, the lobby, laundry, EVERYTHING.

I just moved in 9 months ago and I can't wait to leave.

Management has overturned 3 times since living here for 10 months. Literally would never recommend this place. I am withholding rent currently until they can actually provide habitable conditions--there was no hot water for 2 days.
